# Michurinsk, Sharansky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Michurinsk () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Michurinsky Selsoviet, Sharansky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 328 in 2010. There are seven streets.
Geography
Michurinsk is located 16&nbsp;km northeast of Sharan (the district's administrative centre) by road. Bulansaz is the nearest rural locality.
